Prominent businessman Prince Alex Mbata, has built a two kilometer road in new Owerri area of the Imo State capital. It is a dual carriage way with street lights as approved by the Imo state government. The businessmanâ€™s efforts, according to those close to him, is to complement the onging rehabilitation of roads being carried out by the Uzodimma Administration in Imo State. It is also in line with the philanthropic gestures of Prince Mbata, who has constructed places of worship for his people and a five kilometer road from from Ulakwo to Ngwoma, to make life better for his people Obube community, Owerri North Local government area. It was learnt that Governor Uzodimma hd accepted to inaugurate the project.